  "text": "## Kubernetes - wait.ExponentialBackoff\n\nThe kubernetes/kubernetes repository implements exponential backoff primarily in `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait/backoff.go`. The core function is `ExponentialBackoff(backoff Backoff, condition ConditionFunc)` which repeatedly executes a condition function with exponentially increasing waits between attempts. The `Backoff` struct defines parameters: Duration (initial wait), Factor (multiplier), Jitter (randomization), Steps (max attempts), and Cap (max wait time). For context-aware usage, `ExponentialBackoffWithContext` is provided for cancellable retry loops.\n\nAdditional exponential backoff implementations in Kubernetes include:\n- `exponentialBackoffManagerImpl` (deprecated) in the same backoff.go file\n- `ExponentialBackoff` struct in `pkg/util/goroutinemap/exponentialbackoff/exponential_backoff.go` for tracking operation errors\n- `WithExponentialBackoff` methods in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/util/webhook/webhook.go` for retrying webhook operations\n\n## Grafana - ExponentialBackoffRetrier\n\nGrafana implements exponential backoff retry logic in multiple places:\n\n1. **Git Repository Retrier** (`apps/provisioning/pkg/repository/git/repository.go`): The `defaultGitRetrier()` function creates an `ExponentialBackoffRetrier` configured with 8 total attempts (1 initial + 7 retries), initial delay of 100ms, maximum delay of 5 seconds, exponential multiplier of 2.0, and jitter enabled. This retries network errors, 5xx errors, and 429 rate-limit errors.\n\n2. **Provisioning Resources Retry** (`pkg/registry/apis/provisioning/resources/retry_client.go`): The `retryWithBackoff()` method uses Kubernetes' `wait.ExponentialBackoff` with a `defaultRetryBackoff()` configuration (100ms initial duration, 2.0 factor, 0.1 jitter, 8 steps, 5s cap).\n\n3. **Alert Scheduling Retrier** (`pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/retry.go`): The `newExponentialBackoffRetryer()` function creates an `exponentialBackoffRetryer` wrapping a `backoff.BackOff` implementation with configurable max retries, initial/max delays, randomization factor, and clock provider.\n\n## Prometheus - Remote Write Backoff\n\nPrometheus implements exponential backoff for remote write operations in `storage/remote/queue_manager.go`. The `sendWriteRequestWithBackoff()` function implements retry logic by:\n\n1. Starting with `MinBackoff` duration (default 30ms)\n2. Doubling the backoff on each recoverable error\n3. Capping at `MaxBackoff` (default 5s)\n4. Respecting Retry-After headers when provided by the server\n5. Disabling resharding during active retry backoff to prevent thundering herd\n\nThe `QueueConfig` struct in `config/config.go` defines these backoff parameters alongside retry configuration.\n"
